posts.title: TIPS abdo
posts.written: Wobbly Life is a lively open world physics based sandbox. Explore Wobbly Island with your friends, discover fun locations filled with minigames and dynamic toys. Be a hard working wobbly and work around town in various roles to earn cash to own properties and purchase

posts.title: TIPS 2
posts.written: Play with your friends in Online and Local Co-op up to 4 players Lively Open world Sandbox filled wide variety of mini games toys and vehicles Varied customization of character and vehicles Complete Jobs in the open world to earn funds to unlock clothes vehicles and houses

posts.title: TIPS 3
posts.written: Laid back and relaxed, this is a game I bought two copies of for my kids to pla I didn t expect Id be the one playing it too. There is no real depth to the game but honestly that's a lot of its charm for me I found it more enjoyable than Totally Reliable Deliver Service so far but that's just a personal opinion. UPDATE: Forgot to mention, I have two computers which is why I bought two copies If you have a few xbox one controllers you can also play on the same computer, it supports up to 4 players this way via split screen.

posts.title: TIPS 4
posts.written: I'd describe it as wholesome Grand Theft Auto: nice variety of things to do, stuff to discover, and, of course, it's great with friends. Silly, fun, goofy, can't wait to see it expanded with even more to do and, with any luck, an even larger map. I've already been surprised several times by what there is to find
